1. Introduction

Madzilla Apps ("we", "us", "our") built Mythic Mahjong as a free-to-play mobile game. This Privacy Policy explains what information is collected when you use the app, how it is used, and your rights regarding that information.

2. Information We Collect

We do not ask you to create an account or provide personal information directly.

The following data may be collected automatically through third-party SDKs:

Game progress & settings
Stored only on your device (Room database & DataStore). This data is never sent to our servers.

Advertising data (Google AdMob)
Device identifiers, IP address, and interaction data may be used to serve personalised or non-personalised ads based on your consent.
Google Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy

Analytics (Firebase Analytics)
Anonymous usage events such as screens visited, features used, and session duration. No personally identifiable information is included.

Crash reports (Firebase Crashlytics)
Device model, OS version, and stack traces at the moment of a crash. No personal data is attached.

Performance data (Firebase Performance)
Network latency and app start times. This data is fully anonymous.

3. Ad Consent (GDPR / CCPA)

On first launch, you will see a consent dialog powered by the Google User Messaging Platform (UMP).

You may choose to allow personalised ads or restrict ads to non-personalised ads only.

You can manage or withdraw your consent at any time through your device settings or by reopening the consent form.

4. In-App Purchases

The optional Premium upgrade is handled entirely by the Google Play Store.

We do not collect or store any payment or card information.

5. Children

Mythic Mahjong is not directed at children under the age of 13.

We do not knowingly collect personal data from children.

If you believe a child has provided personal information, please contact us at madzillaapps@gmail.com
 and we will delete it promptly.

6. Data Retention

Local data (progress and settings) remains on your device until you uninstall the app.

Crash and analytics data retained by Firebase follows Google's standard retention policies (typically 90 days).

7. Your Rights

Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the right to access, correct, or delete data associated with you.

Because we do not store identifiable data on our servers, requests should be directed to the relevant third-party services listed below.

For any privacy concerns, contact us at madzillaapps@gmail.com
.

